<br>
Yes my str sucks but I group with my 58 shammy pretty much always so with buffs I'm over 150. I'm on the look out for a pair of valorium ring's of gallantry ( that would be an extra 16str right there ) I'm waiting for the price of these to come down to sane levels though, currently 35k on my server.<br>
<br>
I still need one question answered though, is the zek/horn a viable set-up for exp groups? <br>
<br>
thnx again <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viladdarorcslayer>Viladdar Orcslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/30/02 7:08:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4753.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: viladdar</span><hr size=1> I'd go rather Swiftblade of Zek / Fleshgrinder instead of Zek / Horn. The Horn seems way too expensive to me for what it is worth, and we warriors are nerfed on piercing skill... So, I'd not buy a Horn. Anyway, you shouldn't have any problems to hold aggro just with a Zek / Frosty combo, mine is even worse, you can check it on my magelo. Doesn't look uber at all but works pretty fine. I have serious problems only with non-skilled casters who land their debuffs too early or overnuke.<br>
<br>
About str, mine is around 150 unbuffed, and I dont think that if it was around 100 I would notice a big DPS loss. No, my suggestion was to raise it to ~150 unbuffed BECAUSE of buffs, wich will get you to 200+, and THERE you will get your crazy damage (and much less misses... usually. Depends of course on level / AC of the mobs you are fighting too). <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
